snippet.textDisplay:
Man, there sure is a lot of misinformation in the comments regarding Twitch's ad change.  Twitch already had ads on the site for a very long time with the ability to remove them if you had Amazon Prime (and therefore Twitch Prime).  What they've done is remove that feature from Twitch Prime and added it to Twitch Turbo instead which has similar benefits for a similar price but without all the Amazon stuff and the free monthly subscription.

It is a horrible change, and I will most likely be cancelling my Amazon Prime subscription (and I also encourage viewers to enable adblock), but Twitch having ads is not at all new.  All that changed is that more users will now be seeing those ads that they previously wouldn't have to because they were paying to avoid it.  It sucks immensely for mobile users because there won't be a way to disable ads for the Twitch app without paying for Turbo.

Although I am disappointed with Twitch Prime dropping ad free viewing, there is a little bit of misinformation here. And yes, that was one of the biggest perks, aside from a great amount of people using adblockers which negated it in the first place.

The misinformation howevrr, is that there is nothing left as a perk foe Twitch Prime. You still get a free subscription to any streamer you like, and sometimes you get free games, and quite often you get in game loot for certain popular games. I think it is still a good deal.

Still a bummer with ad free viewing being dropped but, still some good stuff with it, IMO.
